msgctxt "mn60:20.6"
msgid ""
"yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ pāsaṃso, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissati."
msgstr ""
"For they are praised by sensible people in the present life, and when their "
"body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly "
"realm."

msgctxt "mn60:20.7"
msgid ""
"Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo susamatto samādinno, ubhayaṃsaṃ pharitvā "
"tiṭṭhati, riñcati akusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They have rightly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it "
"encompasses the positive outcomes of both sides, leaving out the unskillful "
"premise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.408"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:21.1"
msgid "Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "mn60:21.2"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṃkilesāya;"
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn60:21.3"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason."

msgctxt "mn60:21.4"
msgid "Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr "There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn60:21.5"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason."

#. VAR: vīriyaṃ → viriyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn60:21.6"
msgid ""
"Natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo;"
msgstr "There is no power, no energy, no manly strength or vigor."

#. VAR: avīriyā → … aviriyā (bj, pts1) | sabbe sattā … savasā sabalā saviriyā (s1-3, km) | sabbe sattā … savasā sabalā savīriyā (mr)
msgctxt "mn60:21.7"
msgid ""
"sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā "
"niyatisaṃgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti."
msgstr ""
"All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack "
"control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, "
"they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:22.1"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ujuvipaccanīkavādā."
msgstr ""
"And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts "
"this."

msgctxt "mn60:22.2"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn60:22.3"
msgid "‘atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṃkilesāya;"
msgstr "‘There is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn60:22.4"
msgid "sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted with cause and reason."

msgctxt "mn60:22.5"
msgid "Atthi hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr "There is a cause and condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn60:22.6"
msgid "sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified with cause and reason."

msgctxt "mn60:22.7"
msgid "Atthi balaṃ, atthi vīriyaṃ, atthi purisathāmo, atthi purisaparakkamo;"
msgstr "There is power, energy, manly strength and vigor."

msgctxt "mn60:22.8"
msgid ""
"na sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā "
"niyatisaṃgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti."
msgstr ""
"It is not the case that all sentient beings, all living creatures, all "
"beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy, or that, molded by "
"destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the "
"six classes of rebirth.’"

msgctxt "mn60:22.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo, "
msgstr "What do you think, householders? "

msgctxt "mn60:22.10"
msgid "nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?"
msgstr "Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”"

msgctxt "mn60:22.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:23.1"
msgid "“Tatra, gahapatayo, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr ""
"“Since this is so, consider those ascetics and brahmins whose view is that"

msgctxt "mn60:23.2"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;"
msgstr ""
"there’s no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings, etc."

msgctxt "mn60:23.3"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn60:23.4"
msgid "Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn60:23.5"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn60:23.6"
msgid ""
"Natthi balaṃ, natthi vīriyaṃ, natthi purisathāmo, natthi purisaparakkamo; "
"sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā "
"niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn60:23.7"
msgid ""
"tesametaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—yamidaṃ kāyasucaritaṃ, vacīsucaritaṃ, manosucaritaṃ—"
"ime tayo kusale dhamme abhinivajjetvā yamidaṃ kāyaduccaritaṃ, "
"vacīduccaritaṃ, manoduccaritaṃ—ime tayo akusale dhamme samādāya vattissanti."
msgstr ""
"You can expect that they will reject good conduct by way of body, speech, "
"and mind, and undertake and implement bad conduct by way of body, speech, "
"and mind."

msgctxt "mn60:23.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn60:23.9"
msgid ""
"Na hi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā passanti akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ "
"saṅkilesaṃ, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ vodānapakkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Because those ascetics and brahmins don’t see that unskillful qualities are "
"full of drawbacks, depravity, and corruption, or that skillful qualities "
"have the benefit and cleansing power of renunciation."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:24.1"
msgid ""
"Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ tissa diṭṭhi hoti; sāssa hoti "
"micchādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"Moreover, since there actually is causality, their view that there is no "
"causality is wrong view."

msgctxt "mn60:24.2"
msgid ""
"Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti saṅkappeti; svāssa hoti "
"micchāsaṅkappo."
msgstr ""
"Since there actually is causality, their thought that there is no causality "
"is wrong thought."

msgctxt "mn60:24.3"
msgid ""
"Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti vācaṃ bhāsati; sāssa hoti "
"micchāvācā."
msgstr ""
"Since there actually is causality, their speech that there is no causality "
"is wrong speech."

msgctxt "mn60:24.4"
msgid ""
"Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti āha; ye te arahanto hetuvādā "
"tesamayaṃ paccanīkaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"Since there actually is causality, in saying that there is no causality they "
"contradict those perfected ones who teach that there is causality."

msgctxt "mn60:24.5"
msgid ""
"Santaṃyeva kho pana hetuṃ ‘natthi hetū’ti paraṃ saññāpeti; sāssa hoti "
"asaddhammasaññatti."
msgstr ""
"Since there actually is causality, in convincing another that there is no "
"causality they are convincing them to accept an untrue teaching."

msgctxt "mn60:24.6"
msgid "Tāya ca pana asaddhammasaññattiyā attānukkaṃseti, paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr "And on account of that they glorify themselves and put others down."

msgctxt "mn60:24.7"
msgid ""
"Iti pubbeva kho panassa susīlyaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, dussīlyaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"So they give up their former ethical conduct and are established in "
"unethical conduct."

msgctxt "mn60:24.8"
msgid ""
"ayañca micchādiṭṭhi micchāsaṅkappo micchāvācā ariyānaṃ paccanīkatā "
"asaddhammasaññatti attānukkaṃsanā paravambhanā. Evamassime aneke pāpakā "
"akusalā dhammā sambhavanti micchādiṭṭhipaccayā."
msgstr ""
"And that is how wrong view gives rise to these many bad, unskillful "
"qualities—wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, contradicting the noble "
"ones, convincing others to accept untrue teachings, and glorifying oneself "
"and putting others down."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.409"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:25.1"
msgid "Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati:"
msgstr "A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn60:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘sace kho natthi hetu, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sotthimattānaṃ karissati;"
msgstr ""
"‘If there is no causality, when this individual’s body breaks up they will "
"keep themselves safe."

msgctxt "mn60:25.3"
msgid ""
"sace kho atthi hetu, evamayaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati."
msgstr ""
"And if there is causality, when their body breaks up, after death, they will "
"be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn60:25.4"
msgid ""
"Kāmaṃ kho pana māhu hetu, hotu nesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ "
"vacanaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"But let’s assume that those who say that there is no causality are correct."

msgctxt "mn60:25.5"
msgid ""
"atha ca panāyaṃ bhavaṃ purisapuggalo diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho—"
"dussīlo purisapuggalo micchādiṭṭhi ahetukavādo’ti."
msgstr ""
"Regardless, that individual is still criticized by sensible people in the "
"present life as being an immoral individual of wrong view, one who denies "
"causality.’"

msgctxt "mn60:25.6"
msgid ""
"Sace kho attheva hetu, evaṃ imassa bhoto purisapuggalassa ubhayattha "
"kaliggaho—"
msgstr "But if there really is causality, they lose on both counts."

msgctxt "mn60:25.7"
msgid ""
"yañca diṭṭheva dhamme viññūnaṃ gārayho, yañca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissati."
msgstr ""
"For they are criticized by sensible people in the present life, and when "
"their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn60:25.8"
msgid ""
"Evamassāyaṃ apaṇṇako dhammo dussamatto samādinno, ekaṃsaṃ pharitvā tiṭṭhati, "
"riñcati kusalaṃ ṭhānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They have wrongly undertaken this guaranteed teaching in such a way that it "
"encompasses the positive outcomes of one side only, leaving out the skillful "
"premise."

