#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:31.1"
msgid "“Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati—"
msgstr "“A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn60:31.2"
msgid "ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "‘Some ascetics and brahmins say that"

msgctxt "mn60:31.3"
msgid "‘natthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, idaṃ me adiṭṭhaṃ;"
msgstr "there are no totally formless meditations, but I have not seen that."

msgctxt "mn60:31.4"
msgid "yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Some ascetics and brahmins say that"

msgctxt "mn60:31.5"
msgid "‘atthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, idaṃ me aviditaṃ."
msgstr "there are totally formless meditations, but I have not known that."

#. VAR: Ahañceva → ahañce (?)
msgctxt "mn60:31.6"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana ajānanto apassanto ekaṃsena ādāya vohareyyaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Without knowing or seeing, it would not be appropriate for me to take one "
"side and declare:"

msgctxt "mn60:31.7"
msgid "idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññanti, na metaṃ assa patirūpaṃ."
msgstr "“This is the only truth, other ideas are stupid.”"

msgctxt "mn60:31.8"
msgid "Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "If those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "mn60:31.9"
msgid ""
"‘natthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ "
"vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—"
msgstr "there are no totally formless meditations are correct, it is possible"

msgctxt "mn60:31.10"
msgid "ye te devā rūpino manomayā, apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who possess form and made "
"of mind."

msgctxt "mn60:31.11"
msgid "Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "If those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "mn60:31.12"
msgid ""
"‘atthi sabbaso āruppā’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ "
"vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—"
msgstr "there are totally formless meditations are correct, it is possible"

msgctxt "mn60:31.13"
msgid "ye te devā arūpino saññāmayā, apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who are formless and made "
"of perception."

#. VAR: rūpādhikaraṇaṃ → rūpakāraṇā (mr)
msgctxt "mn60:31.14"
msgid ""
"Dissanti kho pana rūpādhikaraṇaṃ "
"daṇḍādānasatthādānakalahaviggahavivādatuvaṃtuvaṃpesuññamusāvādā."
msgstr ""
"Now, owing to form, bad things are seen: taking up the rod and the sword, "
"quarrels, arguments, and fights, accusations, divisive speech, and lies."

msgctxt "mn60:31.15"
msgid "‘Natthi kho panetaṃ sabbaso arūpe’ti."
msgstr "But those things don’t exist where it is totally formless.’"

msgctxt "mn60:31.16"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya rūpānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting like this, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, "
"and cessation regarding forms."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.411"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:32.1"
msgid "Santi, gahapatayo, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "mn60:32.2"
msgid "‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti."
msgstr "‘There is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:33.1"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃyeva kho, gahapatayo, samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ujuvipaccanīkavādā."
msgstr ""
"And there are some ascetics and brahmins whose doctrine directly contradicts "
"this."

msgctxt "mn60:33.2"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn60:33.3"
msgid "‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti."
msgstr "‘There is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives.’"

msgctxt "mn60:33.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, gahapatayo, "
msgstr "What do you think, householders? "

msgctxt "mn60:33.5"
msgid "nanume samaṇabrāhmaṇā aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā”ti?"
msgstr "Don’t these doctrines directly contradict each other?”"

msgctxt "mn60:33.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:34.1"
msgid "“Tatra, gahapatayo, viññū puriso iti paṭisañcikkhati—"
msgstr "“A sensible person reflects on this matter in this way:"

msgctxt "mn60:34.2"
msgid "ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "‘Some ascetics and brahmins say that"

msgctxt "mn60:34.3"
msgid "‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, idaṃ me adiṭṭhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives, but I have "
"not seen that."

msgctxt "mn60:34.4"
msgid "yepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "Some ascetics and brahmins say that"

msgctxt "mn60:34.5"
msgid "‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, idaṃ me aviditaṃ."
msgstr ""
"there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives, but I have not "
"known that."

msgctxt "mn60:34.6"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana ajānanto apassanto ekaṃsena ādāya vohareyyaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Without knowing or seeing, it would not be appropriate for me to take one "
"side and declare:"

msgctxt "mn60:34.7"
msgid "idameva saccaṃ, moghamaññanti, na metaṃ assa patirūpaṃ."
msgstr "“This is the only truth, other ideas are stupid.”"

msgctxt "mn60:34.8"
msgid "Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "If those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "mn60:34.9"
msgid ""
"‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"saccaṃ vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—"
msgstr ""
"there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives are correct, "
"it is possible"

msgctxt "mn60:34.10"
msgid "ye te devā arūpino saññāmayā apaṇṇakaṃ me tatrūpapatti bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"that I will be guaranteed rebirth among the gods who are formless and made "
"of perception."

msgctxt "mn60:34.11"
msgid "Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "If those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "mn60:34.12"
msgid ""
"‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, sace tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ saccaṃ "
"vacanaṃ, ṭhānametaṃ vijjati—"
msgstr ""
"there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives are correct, it "
"is possible"

msgctxt "mn60:34.13"
msgid "yaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyissāmi."
msgstr "that I will be extinguished in the present life."

msgctxt "mn60:34.14"
msgid "Ye kho te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "The view of those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

#. VAR: sārāgāya → sarāgāya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn60:34.15"
msgid ""
"‘natthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi sārāgāya santike, "
"saṃyogāya santike, abhinandanāya santike, ajjhosānāya santike, upādānāya "
"santike."
msgstr ""
"there is no such thing as the total cessation of future lives is close to "
"greed, approving, attachment, and grasping."

msgctxt "mn60:34.16"
msgid "Ye pana te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "The view of those ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "mn60:34.17"
msgid ""
"‘atthi sabbaso bhavanirodho’ti, tesamayaṃ diṭṭhi asārāgāya santike, "
"asaṃyogāya santike, anabhinandanāya santike, anajjhosānāya santike, "
"anupādānāya santiketi."
msgstr ""
"there is such a thing as the total cessation of future lives is close to non-"
"greed, non-approving, non-attachment, and non-grasping.’"

msgctxt "mn60:34.18"
msgid ""
"So iti paṭisaṅkhāya bhavānaṃyeva nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Reflecting like this, they simply practice for disillusionment, dispassion, "
"and cessation regarding future lives."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya35"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.412"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:35.1"
msgid "Cattārome, gahapatayo, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "Householders, these four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "mn60:35.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. </p><ol><li>
msgctxt "mn60:35.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo attantapo hoti "
"attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"One person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of mortifying "
"themselves."

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "mn60:35.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo parantapo hoti "
"paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"One person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying others."

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "mn60:35.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo attantapo ca hoti "
"attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"One person mortifies themselves and others, committed to the practice of "
"mortifying themselves and others."

#. </li><li>
msgctxt "mn60:35.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo nevattantapo hoti "
"nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;"
msgstr ""
"One person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to the "
"practice of not mortifying themselves or others."

msgctxt "mn60:35.7"
msgid ""
"so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto "
"sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati."
msgstr ""
"They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, "
"experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves."

#. </li></ol><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya36"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:36.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?"
msgstr ""
"And what person mortifies themselves, committed to the practice of "
"mortifying themselves?"

msgctxt "mn60:36.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo acelako hoti muttācāro hatthāpalekhano … pe "
"…"
msgstr "It’s when someone goes naked, ignoring conventions. …"

msgctxt "mn60:36.3"
msgid ""
"iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""
"And so they live committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying "
"and tormenting the body."

msgctxt "mn60:36.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"This is called a person who mortifies themselves, being committed to the "
"practice of mortifying themselves."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya37"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:37.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?"
msgstr ""
"And what person mortifies others, committed to the practice of mortifying "
"others?"

msgctxt "mn60:37.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo orabbhiko hoti sūkariko … pe … ye vā "
"panaññepi keci kurūrakammantā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a person is a butcher of sheep, pigs, poultry, or deer, a hunter "
"or fisher, a bandit, an executioner, a butcher of cattle, a jailer, or has "
"some other cruel livelihood."

msgctxt "mn60:37.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo parantapo paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"This is called a person who mortifies others, being committed to the "
"practice of mortifying others."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya38"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:38.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto "
"parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto?"
msgstr ""
"And what person mortifies themselves and others, being committed to the "
"practice of mortifying themselves and others?"

msgctxt "mn60:38.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, gahapatayo, ekacco puggalo rājā vā hoti khattiyo muddhāvasitto … pe …"
msgstr "It’s when a person is an anointed king or a well-to-do brahmin. …"

msgctxt "mn60:38.3"
msgid "tepi daṇḍatajjitā bhayatajjitā assumukhā rudamānā parikammāni karonti."
msgstr ""
"His bondservants, servants, and workers do their jobs under threat of "
"punishment and danger, weeping, with tearful faces."

msgctxt "mn60:38.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo attantapo ca attaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto "
"parantapo ca paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto."
msgstr ""
"This is called a person who mortifies themselves and others, being committed "
"to the practice of mortifying themselves and others."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:39.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo ca, gahapatayo, puggalo nevattantapo nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto "
"na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;"
msgstr ""
"And what person doesn’t mortify either themselves or others, committed to "
"the practice of not mortifying themselves or others,"

msgctxt "mn60:39.2"
msgid ""
"so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto "
"sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharati?"
msgstr ""
"living without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, "
"experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya40-54"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:40-54.1"
msgid "Idha, gahapatayo, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened "
"Buddha …"

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone "
"reborn in some good family. …"

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.3"
msgid "so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
msgstr ""
"They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.4"
msgid ""
"vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ "
"pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful "
"qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption …"

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.5"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.6"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn60:40-54.7"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya55"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.413"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:55.1"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward recollection of past lives. …"

msgctxt "mn60:55.2"
msgid ""
"So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi "
"jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"They recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

msgctxt "mn60:55.3"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings."

msgctxt "mn60:55.4"
msgid ""
"So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate … pe … "
"yathākammūpage satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient beings "
"passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in "
"a good place or a bad place. … They understand how sentient beings are "
"reborn according to their deeds."

msgctxt "mn60:55.5"
msgid ""
"So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese "
"mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ "
"abhininnāmeti."
msgstr ""
"When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, "
"flawless, rid of imperfections, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—"
"they extend it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn60:55.6"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice "
"that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "mn60:55.7"
msgid "‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They truly understand: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of "
"defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’."

msgctxt "mn60:55.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi "
"cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of "
"sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance."

msgctxt "mn60:55.9"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "mn60:55.10"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya56"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:56.1"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, gahapatayo, puggalo nevattantapo "
"nāttaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto na parantapo na paraparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto;"
msgstr ""
"This is called a person who neither mortifies themselves or others, being "
"committed to the practice of not mortifying themselves or others."

msgctxt "mn60:56.2"
msgid ""
"so anattantapo aparantapo diṭṭheva dhamme nicchāto nibbuto sītībhūto "
"sukhappaṭisaṃvedī brahmabhūtena attanā viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They live without wishes in the present life, extinguished, cooled, "
"experiencing bliss, having become holy in themselves.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya57"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn60:57.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sāleyyakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When he had spoken, the brahmins and householders of Sālā said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn60:57.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "mn60:57.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya "
"‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "mn60:57.4"
msgid ""
"Ete mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāma dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"We go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn60:57.5"
msgid "Upāsake no bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gate”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember us as lay followers who have "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn60:57.6"
msgid "Apaṇṇakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn60:57.7"
